9c165b8c-5bfb-46f1-b229-840cc273ab2f.08e64c25-e815-4004-8f66-2117fef04caa.description=Description\: 

This step utilizes the BEA Smart Update(bsu) command line utility to remove the patches from a given WebLogic Domain.

Return Code\:

0 \= Weblogic instance does not exist
1 \= Step failed.
2 \= Step ran successfully

Inputs\:
 command - executes WebLogicRollbackPatch.py
 BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/WebLogic/Binaries
 Call Wrapper - Required\: Command that will execute the step as a specific user (by default, sudo su - root/opt/opsware/jython/jython on UNIX targets and jython running as Administrator on Windows targets).
 Patch Identifiers - Generated\: List of the patch ids extracted
 WebLogic Instance Exists - True if there is at least one weblogic instance that exists on the server. False otherwise
 WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory in which to install WebLogic Server. For instance /opt/WebLogic/Binaries/wls103he target machine.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Patch Names - Generated\: List of Patches that were applied.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 9c165b8c-5bfb-46f1-b229-840cc273ab2f.description=<pre>
 Purpose

This workflow removes one or more patches from given WebLogic 11g or 12c Server Installation
This workflow uses WLST to connect to admin server to stop the Managed Servers and the Admin Server.
The Servers are stopped only if they are bound to the given WebLogic server installation and are local.
The WLST Enables three ways of Connect\:
 1. Boot Properties file (default)
 2. Username and Password
 3. UserConfigFile and UserKeyFile




 Results verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. The workflow results will indicate whether some or all of the patches were applied successfully. Be sure to also perform the following steps\:

Look at the console output for errors messages that indicate if one or all of the patches was had problems being applied. Specifically look at the WebLogic Patch Server for errors related to applying a specific patch.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 BEA Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the Middleware Home directory that will contain this installation. For instance /opt/oracle/weblogic.
 Patch Rollback List - Required\: Comma separated list of patches to install. Example /opt/wlpatch/p14154043_1035_Generic.zip
 WLS Install Home - Required\: Fully qualified path to the product installation directory of WebLogic Server to be patched. For instance /opt/oracle/weblogic/wlserver12.1

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 WebLogic User Config File - Optional\: This parameter will be used to connect to a webLogic domain using WLST. If Specified, the file path has to be relative to a WebLogic domain path for ex\: /connect/userconfigFile will be expanded as /opt/oracle/weblogic/user_projects/domain_temp/connect/userConfigFile and the same value will be used in WLST Connect in multi domain environment
 WebLogic User Password - Optional\: The WebLogic Admin Password for the a WebLogic domain.This parameter will be used to connect to WebLogic domain using WLST.Same value will be used in WLST Connect in multi domain environment
 WebLogic User Id - Optional\: The WebLogic Admin Username for the a WebLogic domain.This parameter will be used to connect to WebLogic domain using WLST.Same value will be used in WLST Connect in multi domain environment
 Weblogic User Key File - Optional\: This parameter will be used to connect to a webLogic domain using WLST. If Specified, the file path has to be relative to a WebLogic domain path for ex\: /connect/userKeyFile will be expanded as /opt/oracle/weblogic/user_projects/domain_temp/connect/userKeyFile and the same value will be used in WLST Connect in multi domain environment
 Cleanup - Optional\: Specifies if the patch files should be removed after the patch workflow ends

 Dependencies

\# Make sure that Discovery has been run and that metadata is up to date before running the WebLogic patching workflow.
\# Make sure that the patches you are trying to apply are intended to be installed on the correct version of WebLogic 11g or 12c.

	



 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the OTHER FILES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
</pre> 9c165b8c-5bfb-46f1-b229-840cc273ab2f.f58a9470-b9ef-4f9a-b56f-af36bf609fd6.description=Description\:
